column2: Tell us about your experiences with climate change!

column24: Did you participate in the in-person community deliberations held in October 2022?
column25: Which organization recruited you to the site?

column6: The once-lush green forest had turned into a desolate wasteland. The scorching heat had parched the earth, and the absence of rain had caused the rivers to dry up. The animals, who once roamed free, had perished or fled to find new habitats. The people who lived nearby were struggling to survive, as they had lost their means of livelihood. The negative effects of climate change were now impossible to ignore, and the future looked bleak.
